[~isding_l]:  Here is an example. ConsumerGroupHeartbeatResponse has a field Assignment, which is a nullable struct.

{code:java}
    { "name": "Assignment", "type": "Assignment", "versions": "0+", "nullableVersions": "0+", "default": "null",
      "about": "null if not provided; the assignment otherwise.", "fields": [
      { "name": "TopicPartitions", "type": "[]TopicPartitions", "versions": "0+",
        "about": "The partitions assigned to the member that can be used immediately." }
    ]}
{code}

The generated class ConsumerGroupHeartbeatResponseData has the following code for serialization related to a null value.

{code:java}
        if (assignment == null) {
            _writable.writeByte((byte) -1);
        } else {
            _writable.writeByte((byte) 1);
            assignment.write(_writable, _cache, _version);
        }
{code}

